  "time_ut": 1662124261,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db1 \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dba\u0dd2.\u0d91\u0db8\u0dca.\u0d91\u0dc6\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2 \u0db6\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0d9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Political instability puts IMF money distribution at risk",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Fitch Ratings pointed out that political instability poses a risk to the implementation of reforms recommended by the International Monetary Fund and creditors agreeing to debt restructuring and disbursement of funds from the International Monetary Fund.",
        "Fitch Ratings stated that although the government has increased the spending for the society to prevent public opposition, the public's support for the government seems to be weak.",
        "Fitch Ratings said that the need for income tax reform is a key part of the program presented by the International Monetary Fund.",
        "Fitch Ratings stated that the IMF's assistance program appears to signal a sharp shift in policy settings to achieve macroeconomic stability, including reducing the budget gap, flexible exchange rates and the independence of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka.",
        "Fitch Ratings pointed out that the staff agreement will not be approved by the Executive Board until Sri Lanka fulfills the recommendations of the International Monetary Fund. Fitch Ratings said that one of the recommendations is to obtain a financial guarantee of Sri Lanka's debt sustainability from creditors and to reach an agreement with private creditors. The institute said.",
        "Fitch Ratings stated that since the International Monetary Fund has assessed Sri Lanka's debt as unsustainable, the outcome of negotiations with creditors should be based on debt relief.",
        "Fitch Ratings predicted that Sri Lanka's primary surplus will increase by 2.3 percent compared to the gross domestic product by 2024."
      ],
